# `src/scripts` — modules and extraction

Vue SFCs import **pure helpers** from here; [vue-quasar.mdc](vue-quasar.mdc), [code-size-decomposition.mdc](code-size-decomposition.mdc). **Component-owned script logic** not app-wide → **`src/components/<bucket>/<Feature>/scripts/`**, not `src/scripts/`. **Colocated `_data/`** + **test fixtures** (inline in `*.vitest.test.ts` / `*.playwright.test.ts`, not separate `_tests/*.ts` dumps) not under `src/scripts/` — vue-quasar + Vitest/Playwright rules.

## Layout

- **`_utilities/`** — small pure helpers (format, parsing); **JSDoc** each export (`@param` / `@returns` where helpful), e.g. [colorFormatConvertors.ts](src/scripts/_utilities/colorFormatConvertors.ts).
- **`appInternals/`** — cross-cutting renderer helpers in **`rendererAppInternals_manager.ts`**, **`appInternals_manager.ts`** (Storybook canvas detection, Vite public asset paths, interface language apply/save, boot routing) — not feature-dialog/keybind-specific.
- **Feature folders** (e.g. `appGlobalManagementUI/`) — behavior tied to app features; one area per file group.
- **`keybinds/`** — global shortcut matching, chord helpers, **`faKeybindRunCommand`**, user-visible chord labels in **`faKeybindsChordUiFormatting.ts`** (**`formatFaKeybindChordForUi`**, **`formatFaKeybindCommandLabelFromSnapshot`**); wired **`MainLayout.vue`** + **`S_FaKeybinds`**. New app-wide shortcuts: [fantasia-keybinds](../skills/fantasia-keybinds/SKILL.md).
- **`floatingWindows/`** — **`useFaFloatingWindowFrame`**, **`useFaFloatingWindowResize`**, **`useFaFloatingWindowTitleDrag`**, **`faFloatingWindowFrameLayout.ts`**, **`faFloatingWindowResizeGeometry.ts`**, **`faFloatingWindowResizeClamp.ts`**, Quasar transition ref **`faQuasarDialogStandardTransition.ts`**, custom pop **Transition** **`faFloatingWindowPopTransition.ts`**. [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) **In-renderer floating windows**, [fantasia-floating-windows](../skills/fantasia-floating-windows/SKILL.md).
- **`faDragDrop/`** — shared **`vue-draggable-plus`** for vertical tab strips/palette rows (**`buildFaVerticalDraggableTabsRootStyle`**, **`faVerticalDraggableTabsSortableDragOptions`**, drag cursor/ghost). Types: **`types/I_faVerticalDraggableTabs.ts`**. Styles: **`src/css/theme/custom-components/faVerticalDraggableTabs.scss`**. Ref TabLists: **`DialogProjectSettingsWorldsTabList`**, **`DialogProjectSettingsDocumentTemplatesTabList`**. [fantasia-drag-drop](../skills/fantasia-drag-drop/SKILL.md) **Vertical draggable tab strips**.
- **`faColorContrast/`** — hex luminance for picker swatch borders (**`faColorContrast.ts`**); **`FaColorPickerInput`**, **Project Settings** palette swatches.
- **`faIcons/`** — committed q-icon catalogs (**`catalogs/*.catalog.json`**), lazy load + merge, level-1 filter/chunk/merge for **`FaIconPickerInput`**. Regenerate: **`yarn generate:icon-catalogs`**. [fantasia-icon-picker](../skills/fantasia-icon-picker/SKILL.md).
- Leading `_` on folders (e.g. `_utilities`) = shared non-feature helpers.

## When to split a file

**Hard limits** (ESLint; [code-size-decomposition.mdc](code-size-decomposition.mdc)): **`src/scripts/`** `.ts` **≤250 lines**, each function **≤100 lines** (tests: global exemption; shared types under **`types/`** exempt there).

Hard to scan or near caps:

1. **Group by domain** — color vs list/array; no mega `utils.ts`.
2. **Reusable pure functions** → `_utilities/` with clear names.
3. **Electron/renderer boundaries** — `window` / `faContentBridgeAPIs` code next to feature that uses it, not generic utilities unless established.

**Do not over-split:** tiny one-helper files harder to navigate than one domain module under cap. **Merge** related exports until **250 lines** or **100 lines/function** forces split; [code-size-decomposition.mdc](code-size-decomposition.mdc) **Module count** + **Return object literals**.

**Intentionally small modules OK** with **documented** reason — e.g. thin **`faKeybindRunCommand`** file for **`vi.mock`** without mocking whole keydown dispatcher, or breaking circular import. Prefer fixing root cause when cheap; thin file stays → brief file-top/export JSDoc so future edits do not consolidate away seam.

**Vitest `vitest.setup.ts`:** do **not** import **`rendererAppInternals`** — imports **`i18n`** at module top before hoisted **`vi.mock('app/i18n/externalFileLoader')`** can close over **`ref`** stubs. Setup keeps tiny duplicate **`setFantasiaStorybookCanvasFlag`** next to i18n mock (see **`vitest/vitest.setup.ts`** comments).

## Style

- Match import style (`app/...` alias where repo uses it).
- Name exports for **observable behavior** (what callers achieve, store/UI consistency), not metaphor-only labels (**lease** for coordination). Prefer invariant names (**stack**, exclusivity between dialog families) or concrete entry point; short JSDoc when behavior spans stores/open paths (see **`dialogManagement.ts`** under **`appGlobalManagementUI/`**).
- Explicit return types on public exports when surrounding code does.
- No `any` in signatures/shapes/casts; precise types (`unknown` + narrow).
- Unit tests encouraged for `src/scripts/**` in neighboring `_tests/` (`src/scripts/_utilities/_tests/`, etc.) via `*.vitest.test.ts`.
- Playwright for UI integration; do not move renderer interaction coverage out of Playwright when checks depend on built app behavior.
